    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - REMOVE - FLOW SWITCH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FLOW SWITCH</title>
        <para>For electrical diagnostic information, refer to Group 08 - ELECTRICAL in the CTS-5000 Master Service
            Manual.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s04017y_11.xml" xrefid="f0401703">Figure 3</hotlnk>
            for all items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block the vehicle wheels, disconnect battery ground cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a suitable container under the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster unit to catch any power
                steering fluid that may leak out while removing the flow switch (Item 9).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect wiring harness flow switch connector (Item 8) from flow switch (Item 9).</para>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401706">Figure 6</hotlnk>
            for items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unthread the flow switch (Item 1) with O-ring (Item 2) from the Hydro-Max&#8482; booster
                (Item 3).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard O-ring (Item 2) and flow switch (Item 1). They will be replaced with a new O-ring
                and flow switch.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a small magnet, extract the flow switch piston and spring (Items 4 and 5) from the
                Hydro-Max&#8482; booster (Item 3).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401706" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0401726.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Flow Switch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FLOW SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>2. O-RING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BOOSTER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. PISTON</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SPRING</callout1>
                <callout1>6. MASTER CYLINDER</callout1>
                <callout1>7. BACKUP PUMP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
